A '''hernia''' is a condition where an [[Organ (anatomy)|organ]] or [[Tissue (biological)|tissue]] goes into places in the human body that it is not normally in. Most hernias happen in the [[abdomen]]. Hernias sometimes give pain and a lump that can be felt. The cause can be [[hereditary disease|hereditary]] or it can be from lifting objects in a wrong way. There are other things that can give hernias as well.

